fields.quote: “In the end, people don't view their life as merely the average of all its moments—which, after all, is mostly nothing much plus some sleep. For human beings, life is meaningful because it is a story. A story has a sense of a whole, and its arc is determined by the significant moments, the ones where something happens. Measurements of people's minute-by-minute levels of pleasure and pain miss this fundamental aspect of human existence. A seemingly happy life maybe empty. A seemingly difficult life may be devoted to a great cause. We have purposes larger than ourselves.”
fields.author: Atul Gawande

fields.quote: “Brené Brown says that ‘Courage is to tell the story of who you are with your whole heart’; to me that says both courage and strength are needed to help break through scar tissue received from the past.  Ultimately, the reward is a chance to renew and to love once again”
fields.author: Frank Church

fields.quote: “We must be willing to get rid of the life we planned, so as to have the life that is waiting for us.”
fields.author: Joseph Campbell

fields.quote: "The burden of living one's own life is experiencing sensations that no one else can share.”
fields.author: David Ignatow

fields.quote: “Courage doesn’t always roar. Sometimes courage is the little voice at the end of the day that says I’ll try again tomorrow.”
fields.author: Mary Anne Radmacher

fields.quote: “I start each day with a single simple plan: This is going to be a good day. I remain hopeful not hopeless, positive not negative, happy not sad, driven not complacent, and educated not naïve.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Believe in yourself and all that you are. Know that there is something inside you that is greater than any obstacle."
fields.author: Christian D. Larson

fields.quote: “What oxygen is to the lungs, such is hope to the meaning of life.”
fields.author: Emil Brunner

fields.quote: "You've got to get to the stage in life where going for it is more important than winning or losing.”
fields.author: Arthur Ashe

fields.quote: “The measure of who we are is what we do with what we have.”
fields.author: Vince Lombardi

fields.quote: “I choose to make the rest of my life the best of my life.”
fields.author: Louise Hay

fields.quote: “The most beautiful people I’ve known are those who have known trials, have known struggles, have known loss, and have found their way out of the depths.”
fields.author: Elisabeth Kübler-Ross

fields.quote: “Perhaps I am stronger than I think.”
fields.author: Thomas Merton

fields.quote: “Some days are better, some days are worse. Look for the blessing instead of the curse. Be positive, stay strong, and get enough rest. You can’t do it all, but you can do your best.”
fields.author: Doe Zantamata

fields.quote: “Ask yourself what problem you have right now. Not next year, tomorrow or five minutes from now. You can always cope with the now, but you can never cope with the future. Nor do you have to. The answer, the strength and the right action will be there when you need it. Not before or after.”
fields.author: Eckhart Tolle

fields.quote: “You gain strength, courage, and confidence by every experience in which you really stop to look fear in the face. You are able to say to yourself, ‘I lived through this horror. I can take the next thing that comes along.”
fields.author: Eleanor Roosevelt

fields.quote: “There is no medicine like hope, no incentive so great, and no tonic so powerful as expectation of something tomorrow.”
fields.author: Orison Swett Marden

fields.quote: “The most authentic thing about us is our capacity to create, to overcome, to endure, to transform, to love and to be greater than our suffering.”
fields.author: Ben Okri

fields.quote: “You do not need to know precisely what is happening, or exactly where it is all going. What you need is to recognize the possibilities and challenges offered by the present moment, and to embrace them with courage, faith and hope.”
fields.author: Thomas Merton

fields.quote: “Affliction comes to us, not to make us sad but sober; not to make us sorry but wise.”
fields.author: H.G. Wells

fields.quote: “Courage is not having the strength to go on; it is going on when you don’t have the strength.”
fields.author: Theodore Roosevelt

fields.quote: “Being mindful brings us to dwell only on the immediate time, the current moment.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “Here’s a simple mindfulness experience: simply be aware of the steam leaving your morning cup of coffee/tea, clear your immediate thoughts, then sip, focus and savor this moment.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “The current moment was a gift to you. Your life is composed of many such moments. Be mindful of this time. Enjoy it. Embrace it. Live it fully.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “The simplest view of mindfulness is to be aware of what is happening right now, unable to change this time but to embrace the current moment.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote:
“I’ve always made a total effort, even when the odds seemed entirely against me. I never quit trying; I never felt that I didn’t have a chance to win.” Arnold Palmer

“The most rewarding things you do in life are often the ones that look like they cannot be done.” Arnold Palmer

“I look back, it taught me something – it taught me how to live, how to be a better guy, not let defeat be the end of my life.”
fields.author: Arnold Palmer

fields.quote: "Resolve never to quit, never to give up, no matter what the situation."
fields.author: Jack Nicklaus

fields.quote: "If you want to hit it farther, hit it better."
fields.author: Jack Nicklaus

fields.quote: "Focus on remedies, not faults."
fields.author: Jack Nicklaus

fields.quote: "Talent isn't as important as the work and dedication necessary to become competent."
fields.author: Jack Nicklaus

fields.quote:
“I started to complain that my shot was going to into the water.
My friend Kevin Carroll said,
Come on, Yogi, don't be like that.
Think positively."
I replied.
'Okay, I'm positive my shot is going into the water.’”
fields.author: Yogi Berra

fields.quote: “Taking life as it comes, mindful to remain in the present moment is so vital to thriving (and living) with Parkinson’s.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “With Parkinson’s you have two choices: You can let it control you, or you can control it. And I’ve chosen to control it.”
fields.author: US Senator Isakson

fields.quote: “I often say now I don’t have any choice whether or not I have Parkinson’s, but surrounding that non-choice is a million other choices that I can make.”
fields.author: Michael J. Fox

fields.quote: “With the support of my family and friends, I will meet this challenge with the same determination and unwavering intensity that I have displayed in all of my endeavors in life.”
fields.author: Kirk Gibson

fields.quote: “I can’t give my Parkinson’s back but being in the moment alters the lens-of-life for that moment, my mind is focused on the event.  The calming and cleansing effect of mindfulness is a feeling of holism (complete and healthy self).”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “For me, living with Parkinson’s has enhanced my recognition of contentment, gratitude and mindfulness. A simple life-changing goal is to continue to embrace them, and to more effectively use them for their positive effect on the rest of my days. Namaste.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “Stay in the present moment:  Life is always fluid, constantly moving.  Your Parkinson’s is always present, yes, it’s a nuisance. Being able to focus on the current moment, whether good or bad, hard or easy, is better; don’t complicate the thought focusing on yesterday, tomorrow, or your disorder.  Try to stay in the present moment.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “Never give up. It's like breathing—once you quit, your flame dies letting total darkness extinguish every last gasp of hope. You can't do that. You must continue taking in even the shallowest of breaths, continue putting forth even the smallest of efforts to sustain your dreams. Don't ever, ever, ever give up.”
fields.author: Richelle E. Goodrich

fields.quote: “Strength is not measured in muscle, but in will.”
fields.author: Margaret M. Morrow

fields.quote: “Don’t give up. Reach down inside of you and you’ll find something left.”
fields.author: Coach Bear Bryant

fields.quote: “Don’t give up. Don’t ever give up.”
fields.author: Jim Valvano

fields.quote: “Hard times don’t create heroes. It is during the hard times when the ‘hero’ within us is revealed.”
fields.author: Bob Riley

fields.quote: “Hope begins in the dark, the stubborn hope that if you just show up and try to do the right thing, the dawn will come. You wait and watch and work; you don’t give up.”
fields.author: Anne Lamott

fields.quote: “Don’t Give Up: Your life comes with obstacles. We are guaranteed nothing. We live with Parkinson’s, and our paths are rockier, less gentle. Yet, your persistence, perseverance, and determination smooth out each road you travel. When you accept the spirit of not giving in and don’t give up, you embrace your life and strengthen your effort in the presence of Parkinson’s. So, don’t give up, don’t give in, never surrender to Parkinson’s, ever onward.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “This diagnosis is a reminder that this is the life you've got. And you're not getting another one. Whatever has happened, you have to take this growth and treasure and protect it.”
fields.author: Elizabeth Edwards

fields.quote: “When nothing seems to help, I go and look at a stonecutter hammering away at his rock, perhaps a hundred times without as much as a crack showing in it. Yet at the hundred and first blow it will split in two, and I know it was not that last blow that did it, but all that had gone before.”
fields.author: Jacob A. Riis

fields.quote: “You may be the only person left who believes in you, but it’s enough. It takes just one star to pierce a universe of darkness. Never give up.”
fields.author: Richelle E. Goodrich

fields.quote: “The Constancy of the Fight: Carl Yastrzemski, said it nicely with this comment, ‘The race doesn’t always belong to the swift nor the battle to the strong. It belongs rather to those who run the race, who stay the course and who fight the good fight.’ This says to me, you may not be the best-equipped person to mount a challenge to your own Parkinson’s. But having the willpower and bringing the best effort you can give is what it takes to maintain your edge in the fight against your disorder.”
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: “Because you are alive, everything is possible.”
fields.author: Thich Nhat Hanh

fields.quote: The body achieves what the mind believes.”
fields.author: Jim Evans

fields.quote: "What we know matters but who we are matters more"
fields.author: Brené Brown

fields.quote: “I want to be in the arena. I want to be brave with my life. And when we make the choice to dare greatly, we sign up to get our asses kicked. We can choose courage or we can choose comfort, but we can’t have both. Not at the same time. Vulnerability is not winning or losing; it’s having the courage to show up and be seen when we have no control over the outcome. Vulnerability is not weakness; it’s our greatest measure of courage.
fields.author: Brené Brown

fields.quote: "Hope is a function of struggle."
fields.author: Brené Brown

fields.quote: “Crazy-busy' is a great armor, it's a great way for numbing. What a lot of us do is that we stay so busy, and so out in front of our life, that the truth of how we're feeling and what we really need can't catch up with us.”
fields.author: Brené Brown

fields.quote: “If we want to cultivate hopefulness, we have to be willing to be flexible and demonstrate perseverance. Not every goal will look and feel the same. Tolerance for disappointment, determination, and a belief in self are the heart of hope.”
fields.author: Brené Brown

fields.quote: "Joy is not a constant. It comes to us in moments - often ordinary moments. Sometimes we miss out on the bursts of joy because we're too busy chasing down the extraordinary moments. Other times we're so afraid of the dark we don't dare let ourselves enjoy the light. A joyful life is not a floodlight of joy. That would eventually become unbearable. I believe a joyful life is made up of joyful moments gracefully strung together by trust, gratitude and inspiration."
fields.author: Brené Brown

fields.quote: "Whether we're overcoming adversity, surviving trauma, or dealing with stress and anxiety, having a sense of purpose, meaning, and perspective in our lives allows us to develop understanding and move forward. Without purpose, meaning, and perspective, it is easy to lost hope, numb our emotions, or become overwhelmed by our circumstances..."
fields.author: Brené Brown

fields.quote: "What matters the most is your effort."
fields.author: Anonymous

fields.quote: "Once you choose hope, anything's possible."
fields.author: Christopher Reeve

fields.quote: "The thought of hope is the seed to healing."
fields.author: Shilpa Menon

fields.quote: "What oxygen is to the lungs, such is hope to the meaning of life."
fields.author: Emil Brunner

fields.quote: "The important thing is to keep the fire in your heart and be strong to overcome hard moments."
fields.author: Paulo Coelho

fields.quote: "When we least expect it, life sets us a challenge to test our courage and willingness to change; at such a moment, there is no point in pretending that nothing has happened or in saying that we are not yet ready. The challenge will not wait. Life does not look back. A week is more than enough time for us to decide whether or not to accept our destiny."
fields.author: Paulo Coelho

fields.quote: "Be proud of your scars. They remind you that you have the will to live."
fields.author: Paulo Coelho

fields.quote: "Don't allow your wounds to transform you into someone you are not."
fields.author: Paulo Coelho

fields.quote: "I will be capable of loving, regardless of whether I am loved in return, Of giving, when I have nothing, Of working happily, even in the midst of difficulties, Of holding out my hand, even when utterly alone and abandoned, Of drying my tears, even while I weep, Of believing, even when no one believes in me."
fields.author: Paulo Coelho

fields.quote: "This says to me your love, resilience, absolute strength of character and determination will buffer you now until the pain of this storm resolves."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Notice that the stiffest tree is most easily cracked, while the bamboo or willow survives by bending with the wind."
fields.author: Bruce Lee

fields.quote: "This says to me that your ability to adapt, withstand stress, not wither when attacked emotionally will make you a survivor of the heart and someone worth loving."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "The current moment was a gift to you. Your life is composed of many such moments. Be mindful of this time. Enjoy it. Embrace it. Live it fully."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Hope warms you in the winter, provides light in the dark, bird song in the spring morning, and a cool wisp of breeze in the summer. Your ability to resist Parkinson's is buoyed by hope."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "We must remain hopeful as it provides the foundation that you with your loved-ones, family, friends, colleagues and healthcare team are making a difference dealing with your Parkinson's."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "You asked me the other night, 'How did I feel?' I replied that I felt great. My body, my mind, and my thoughts were clear, calm, and in the present moment. I may stumble but I will not fall. To live this way requires persistence, clarity of the moment, and bolstered with a foundation supported by hope."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Wake up each morning full of hope. Finish each day full of gratitude."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "We all face hardship in our lifetime. When something like Parkinson's comes around, you need to stand firm and rise above this disorder by giving it all of your strength and resistance."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Be positive, you can make a difference. Strive for no disease progression and keep working because even a small amount of progress is still far better than progression. Stay positive."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Your mantra against Parkinson's should include some combination of these phrases: 'I will not give up, I will never quit, I will remain mindful, and life is too important to give in to this disorder.' OK?"
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Love fuels your soul, yet it can drive you crazy and increase your anxiety. Love can also provide the bandage that permanently heals the wound on your heart."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "The Beatles had it right when they sang 'And in the end, The love you take. Is equal to the love you make.' Wear your love on your heart."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "If you give it a chance, Parkinson's will change your life. But you can use exercise to plan a new life-path that will keep you healthy for many years to come. Get busy, get active, and stay that way."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "You still control your health, including the path to follow and the response to your disorder. You can still combine the best ingredients to make a salve to help repair the damage from Parkinson's."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Your attitude with Parkinson's needs you to be steely-eyed determined and focused to recognize the miniscule changes that happen over a long period of time."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "The road of your life will take many paths and go through many intersections. Your life-map will be different from my life-map. However, we have the same carry-on luggage named Parkinson's and how it weighs us down will affect the life-path we follow. Stay strong, focused, and persistent. Journey on."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "I acknowledge my Parkinson's, but I refuse to let it define me. I accept that my life, work, and leisure time will remain focused for years to come with my disorder in the background."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Acknowledge your Parkinson's. Try not to let it control your daily response to life. You are still in charge. Remember, you are still you."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Each new morning restarts your life to help manage your Parkinson's. Each new morning stirs the embers to start a new fire to enable your daily gulp of courage to live strong with your disorder."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Stay focused and determined; strive for health and strength. And through it all, try to incorporate happiness into your daily life to help manage your Parkinson's."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Our most difficult life-challenges could create the greatest time of our lives. Staying persistent is creating new options, and it continually requires the courage of one's convictions."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Each day presents an opportunity for Parkinson's to gain more control. Your daily persistence helps to block and slow this maneuver. Keep breathing and living."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Your jar-of-hope will be challenged daily by Parkinson's; hopefully, you'll keep the jar at least half-filled and not half-empty of hope."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Living with Parkinson's takes courage because your enemy is within you, and you always feel its presence. Thus, your hourly-daily-effort to live fully is a measure of your courage."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "I am convinced that gratitude will lead you to the fountain of hope; it is good for your heart, soul, mind, and practicing gratitude will be beneficial for your life with Parkinson's."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "The door to life opens and begins fresh each day. Therefore, as you enter the day, embrace the events knowing that the challenge of Parkinson's remains. Remember, no matter the impact of the disorder on you; you remain you."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "I start each day with a single simple plan: 'This is going to be a good day'... I remain hopeful not hopeless, positive not negative, happy not sad, driven not complacent, and educated not naive."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Life with Parkinson's is best lived in the current moment without either focusing on the past or dreading the future."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "It almost seems that exercise made the brain behave like a molecular sieve to filter out the toxic oligomeric α-synuclein protein and it accumulated in the bloodstream. Exercise works by slowing the progression of Parkinson's."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "The hopeful goal is that exercising will give you healthier lives, allowing one to negotiate a better life on your terms, not Parkinson's."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Be an inspiration for other people-with-Parkinson's such that they might say, because of you, I did not give up."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Perseverance is more than just a word. It is more than a feeling. It is more than a feeling. It is a response to a life experience."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Perseverance is an attitude you take when you won't give up. Perseverance enables you to live your life forward. It functions by strengthening your inner self."
fields.author: Frank C. Church

fields.quote: "Perseverance is a beacon in the tunnel ahead. It will focus you when the odds are against you. It allows you to have a better quality-of-life."
fields.author: Frank C. Church
